s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 25 Apr 2017 09:07:09 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:471:\"\n		        It&#8217;s time to welcome our fifth group of WordCamp Europe speakers! They&#8217;ll be sharing best practices in security, performance, and development tools. Put your hands together for Borek Bernard, Otto Kekäläinen, Oleksandr Strikha, Mark Jaquith, and Miriam Schwab. Borek Bernard &#8211; &#8230; Continue reading Fifth Group of #WCEU speakers &#8211; Borek Bernard, Otto Kekäläinen, Oleksandr Strikha, Mark Jaquith, Miriam Schwab  &#8594;		        \";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"WordCamp Europe\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4799:\"<div id=\"attachment_4840\" style=\"width: 1410px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-4840\" src=\"http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/files/2017/04/wceu-speakers-group-5.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1400\" height=\"800\" /><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">We would like to welcome our fifth group of WordCamp Europe speakers – Borek Bernard, Otto Kekäläinen, Oleksandr Strikha, Mark Jaquith, and Miriam Schwab</p></div>\n<p>It&#8217;s time to welcome our fifth group of WordCamp Europe speakers! They&#8217;ll be sharing best practices in security, performance, and development tools. Put your hands together for Borek Bernard, Otto Kekäläinen, Oleksandr Strikha, Mark Jaquith, and Miriam Schwab.</p>\n<p><span id=\"more-4739\"></span></p>\n<h2>Borek Bernard &#8211; Git in 10 minutes</h2>\n<p>If you know you should be using version control for your WordPress projects but haven&#8217;t started yet then &#8220;<a href=\"http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/session/git-in-10-minutes/\">Git in 10 minutes</a>&#8221; is for you. <a href=\"http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/speaker/borek-bernard/\">Borek</a>, a developer on VersionPress who is passionate about proper tooling, will show you that Git is not scary and that you can actually get started in under 10 minutes.</p>\n<h2>Otto Kekäläinen &#8211; Improving WordPress performance with XDebug and PHP profiling</h2>\n<p>As a software developer and the CEO of Seravo Oy, <a href=\"http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/speaker/otto-kekalainen/\">Otto</a> has valuable insight into both the technical and business needs of a web project. At WordCamp Europe, he will discuss &#8220;<a href=\"http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/session/improving-wordpress-performance-with-xdebug-and-php-profiling\">Improving WordPress performance with XDebug and PHP profiling</a>.&#8221; He&#8217;ll explain how to use XDebug with Webgrind, how to find potential optimisation targets, show examples of real cases when XDebug helped fix a performance problem and also explain what XDebug is not suitable for and what can be used instead. If you are not a developer, you’ll learn what XDebug is capable of and when to ask a developer to use it.</p>\n<h2>Oleksandr Strikha &#8211; Web Fonts Performance</h2>\n<p><a href=\"http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/speaker/oleksandr-strikha/\">Oleksandr</a> is a technical leader of WordPress projects who has designed and led the development of some of the largest content platforms and startups within Scandinavia. Web fonts are a key factor in the speed and lightness of web applications, something which is especially important in the era of mobile devices that we live in. In &#8220;<a href=\"http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/session/web-fonts-performance/\">Web Font Performance</a>,&#8221; Oleksandr will talk about the general problems of loading and rendering fonts in different browsers, and also tools that help solve these problems.</p>\n<h2>Mark Jaquith &#8211; Security is a Process</h2>\n<p><a href=\"http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/speaker/mark-jaquith/\">Mark</a> is a Lead Developer for WordPress core and has been working on WordPress since 2004. In his talk, you will learn that &#8220;<a href=\"http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/session/security-is-a-process/\">Security is a Process</a>&#8221; and a mindset, not merely a plugin that you install. You&#8217;ll then learn how to best protect your sites and yourself from the multitude of threats they face on the Wild Wild Web.</p>\n<h2>Miriam Schwab &#8211; WordPress security for all: you won&#8217;t believe how simple it can be</h2>\n<p>In &#8220;<a href=\"http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/session/wordpress-security-for-all-you-wont-believe-how-simple-it-can-be\">WordPress security for all: you won&#8217;t believe how simple it can be</a>,&#8221; <a href=\"http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/speaker/miriam-schwab/\">Miriam</a> is set to share insights that her and her team at illuminea have picked up after a decade of hosting and maintaining WordPress sites. She&#8217;ll explain a few simple measures that site owners can take to cover 90% of security issues. Miriam will also provide an overview of tools and tweaks that can harden and protect your sites even more.</p>\n<hr />\n<h2>Get your ticket today</h2>\n<p>If you haven&#8217;t already, don&#8217;t forget to get <a href=\"http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/tickets/\">your WordCamp Europe ticket</a>. Your WordCamp Europe ticket covers both days of the conference &#8211; June 16 and 17th &#8211; and contributor day on Thursday, June 15th. It grants you <strong>access to all sessions, lunch, coffee breaks, and the after party</strong>. It also includes an exclusive #WCEU 2017 <strong>t-shirt, stickers, and other great swag</strong>.</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpfr/~4/cA7qw2LTYF0\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:148:\"https://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/2017/04/25/fifth-group-of-wceu-speakers-borek-bernard-otto-kekalainen-oleksandr-strikha-mark-jaquith-miriam-schwab/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:84:\"\n		        \n		        \n		        \n		        \n		        \n		        \n		        \n		    \";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:4:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"Améliorer les sticky posts\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpfr/~3/PrK-oQwBboQ/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://wabeo.fr/ameliorer-sticky-posts/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 25 Apr 2017 08:07:02 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:471:\"\n		        Aujourd’hui je vous propose de découvrir quelques astuces autour d’une fonctionnalité de WordPress trop rarement exploitée&#160;: les sticky posts, ou articles à la Une. Que sont les sticky posts&#160;? Il s’agit d’un système apparu dans